The paper deals with matroids, which are a fundamental concept in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The main focus is on perturbed graphic matroids, which are a specific type of matroid that can be represented by a graph (cs.CG). The paper also studies parameterized complexity, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.DS, cs.CC). Finally, the paper deals with problems related to Steiner Tree and Multiway Cut, which are topics in graph theory and combinatorial optimization (cs.GT).
